10.body: The system has pages such as: Users login page Overview Request Pass Request Electives Make Donations Account Detailed information on each section is provided below. Users login page Authorisation and Authentication page. For authentication and authorisation, you can use several options: Register. Sign in if you already have an account. Sign in using the Innopolis University authentication system if you have a corporate account. Login page Overview After successfully logging in to your account, you will be taken to the Overview section. In this section on the left side there is a menu to navigate between the sections. Also on this page are brief descriptions of the sections. Overview Request Pass This page is designed to generate and send enquiries. You can fill in the necessary forms and send a request if you have a need. In the right part of the page there is background information on popular issues. Overview Once you have completed the form, your enquiry will appear in the History section. Here you can track the status of your enquiry and find out more details. Overview For even more detailed information you can click on an enquiry and see an enquiry card with detailed information about the enquiry. Overview Request Electives This page is designed to generate and send requests for elective courses. You can select the available electives and submit a course request. Overview Overview You can also track the history of requests at the bottom of the section and track the status of requests. Also, if you click on a request, you can read detailed information. Overview Make Donations This section provides information about the possibility of donations. The main part of the section provides detailed information and motivation for action. Overview At the bottom of the section are the necessary details and donation forms. Overview Account This section provides detailed information about the account you are using. You can also update the account data here. Overview

11.body: As an administrator responsible for overseeing the operations and functionalities of the inno-alumni-portal, this guide provides valuable insights into managing user data, processing pass requests, overseeing elective course registrations, and addressing user feedback. You'll find detailed instructions and best practices to streamline administrative tasks and ensure a seamless experience for all users.
11.title: For administrators

12.body: The system has pages such as: Admins login page Overview Pass Requests Manage Elective Courses Manage Donation Account Detailed information on each section is provided below. Admins login page System login page. You need to have an admin account to log in to authenticate and authorise. Overview Overview After authentication and authorisation, you are taken to the main page. Here you can see the data of the last logged in users. Overview Pass Requests This page contains requests from users. Here you can see the dates and statuses of the requests. Overview You can click on the required enquiry for more information and to complete the enquiry response form. Overview Manage Elective Courses This section is similar to the previous one, but belongs to the elective courses section. Here you can familiarise yourself with user requests. Overview To respond to a request, you need to fill in the response form, which can be opened by clicking on the request. Overview Manage Donation In this section we can update the information about donations, as well as review the donations that have come in. Overview By clicking on a specific donation, we can get more detailed information about the selected donation. Overview Account This section provides information about the users of the system. You can also add new users with the required access by clicking the add button in the upper right corner of the screen. Overview

18.body: Using Python Open a shell/command line in the backend folder (preferably after activating a Python virtual environment). Install the required Python packages: pip install -r requirements.txt Run the Python script: python3 main.py Using Docker Here, the image tag name is alumni-backend; you can name it as you like. Also, the default port in Docker is 8000, and locally, you can map it to any port as you like. Build the Docker image: docker build -t alumni-backend Run the Docker container, mapping port 8000 to the desired port: docker run -p 8000:8000 -d alumni-backend
18.title: How to Run

2.body: The inno-alumni-portal serves as a dedicated website aimed at facilitating various services for the alumni community of Innopolis University. It offers alumni the opportunity to stay updated with university events, register for elective courses, manage attendance, and request passes for accessing university facilities. Customer Complaints One of the notable features of the system is its seamless integration for customer feedback and complaint submission. Users can directly submit their complaints through the designated Telegram group mentioned on the website. Users Data Management Administrators have the authority to manage user data effectively. They can review and process requests from users, providing feedback or taking necessary actions such as acceptance or denial based on specific reasons. Pass Order Alumni users have the convenience of requesting passes to access university facilities for various purposes directly from the main page of the website. This streamlined process enhances accessibility and convenience for the alumni community. Elective Courses Participation Requests Another significant aspect of the inno-alumni-portal is its functionality allowing alumni users to request participation in elective courses offered by the university. Through this feature, alumni can express their interest and attend courses relevant to their preferences and schedules.
2.title: Project Description
